<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 1: Create UpgradeModal component</name>
  <files>src/components/ui/UpgradeModal.tsx</files>
  <action>
Create `src/components/ui/UpgradeModal.tsx` — a reusable centered glassmorphism modal following the StageEditModal pattern (NOT Radix Dialog).

**Props interface:**
```typescript
interface UpgradeModalProps {
  isOpen: boolean;
  onClose: () => void;
  onUpgradeClick: () => void;  // Parent handles toast
}
```

**Structure:**
1. If `!isOpen` return null (early exit)
2. Fixed backdrop: `fixed inset-0 bg-black/30 backdrop-blur-sm z-50` with `onClick={onClose}`
3. Fixed centered container: `fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center pointer-events-none`
4. Inner card: `pointer-events-auto w-full max-w-md mx-4` with `dir="rtl"`
5. `GlassCard` with `rounded-3xl shadow-2xl`

**Content (all Hebrew RTL, font-brand body, font-danidin headings):**
- Header: Crown/star icon from lucide-react (`Crown` or `Sparkles`), title "שדרגו לגרסה המלאה" in `font-danidin text-xl`
- Benefits list (3 items, each with a checkmark icon in violet-600):
  - "אורחים ללא הגבלה" (unlimited guests)
  - "ייבוא וייצוא אקסל" (Excel import/export)
  - "אוטומציית וואטסאפ" (WhatsApp automation)
- CTA button: "שדרגו עכשיו" in `bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-700 text-white rounded-xl px-6 py-3 w-full font-medium` — onClick calls `onUpgradeClick` then `onClose`
- Close/dismiss link below: "אולי אחר כך" (maybe later) in `text-slate-500 text-sm` — onClick calls `onClose`

**Escape key handling:** `useEffect` with `keydown` listener when `isOpen` is true. Call `onClose` on Escape. Clean up listener on unmount/close.

**Typography:** Use `font-brand` for body text and benefits, `font-danidin` for the heading.
**Color:** Violet-600 accent, slate neutrals — matching project palette.
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>npx tsc --noEmit src/components/ui/UpgradeModal.tsx 2>&1 | head -20</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>UpgradeModal.tsx exists, exports default component, TypeScript compiles without errors, uses GlassCard pattern with Hebrew RTL content and 3 premium benefits listed</done>
</task>

<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 2: Make Timeline tab always visible in DashboardNav</name>
  <files>src/components/dashboard/DashboardNav.tsx</files>
  <action>
In `src/components/dashboard/DashboardNav.tsx`, remove the gateKey-based filtering so the Timeline tab is always visible.

**Change 1:** Set the Timeline tab's `gateKey` to `null`:
```typescript
// Before:
{ path: '/dashboard/timeline', label: 'ציר זמן', gateKey: 'canAccessTimeline' as const },
// After:
{ path: '/dashboard/timeline', label: 'ציר זמן', gateKey: null },
```

**Why:** Phase 5 requires draft users to SEE the Timeline tab, click it, and see a premium placeholder inside AutomationTimeline.tsx (PAY-01, handled in Plan 03). If the tab is hidden, users can never discover the feature.

**Cleanup:** Since no tabs now use gateKey for filtering, the filter on line 16 becomes a no-op. You MAY simplify: remove the `useFeatureAccess` import and the filter line, just use `ALL_TABS` directly in the map. However, keep the `ALL_TABS` array structure (with `gateKey: null` on all entries) so future phases can re-add gating if needed.

Actually, keep the filter line and useFeatureAccess import — they cost nothing and preserve the pattern for future use. Just change the gateKey to null.
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>npx tsc --noEmit src/components/dashboard/DashboardNav.tsx 2>&1 | head -20</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>Timeline tab (ציר זמן) renders in DashboardNav for all users regardless of event status. The gateKey for Timeline is null.</done>
</task>

